  "texts": [
    "We refer to the collection M as a guarantee, and the researcher only knows the text generator satisfies this guarantee (e.g., it could be any text generator that receives a score of at least 330 on the GRE).",
    "Given an LLM with guarantee M, the researcher would like to draw their conclusions in the prediction problem based on the sample average loss.",
    "Definition 1.",
    "The large language model m(•;t) with guarantee M generalizes in the research context Q(•) if, for all text generators satisfying the guarantee m(•)∈M,",
    "The large language model m(•;t) with guarantee M is a general-purpose technology for prediction if it generalizes in all research contexts Q(•)∈Q."
